news.title: Bengaluru: BDA to fast-track applications from revenue site owners in Dr Shivaram Karanth layout
news.para: The layout, which is spread across 17 villages between Doddaballapura and Hesaraghatta, is likely to accommodate 22,000 sites of various dimensions

news.title: Kerala to ramp up cement production in PSUs to bring down construction cost
news.para: Responding to a calling attention motion by Sunny Joseph MLA, the minister said the state is manufacturing only 10% of the cement required here and 90% of the cement market of the state is being controlled by private companies outside the state.

news.title: Kerala government earns Rs 447 crore through land conversion
news.para: ​​As per this, no permission is required for constructing a house of area 120sq m in 10 cents and for constructing a commercial building of 40sq m in five cents of converted land.

news.title: Indore records Rs 842 crore revenue from property sales in Apr-Oct 2021
news.para: District registrar Balkrishna More said, "Property sales have started on a very good note this fiscal. Revenues have gone up and income in the April-October period was up by 72 per cent as against the same period a year ago."

news.title: Nashik civic body to start work on mall projects soon after Diwali
news.para: Municipal commissioner Kailas Jadhav told TOI that the civic body will prepare a detailed project report (DPR) through an agency which will be deployed after Diwali.

news.title: After over 20 years, Goa government nixes lease deed with Indian Resort Hotels
news.para: After a long tussle, the Goa government has terminated the 1997 lease deed with Indian Resort Hotels Ltd — now known as the Indian Hotels Company Ltd (IHCL) — to set-up recreational facilities for tourists on over 3 lakh sqm land at Aguada plateau.

news.title: Punjab CM offers financial aid of Rs 3,100 each for registered construction workers
news.para: ​"The financial grant of Rs 3,100 is a 'shagun' for construction workers and their families on the joyous festival of lights," Charanjit Singh Channi said.

news.title: Geberit's operating profit rise 1.5% to 230.7 million francs in July-Sept 2021
news.para: Geberit said its bill for raw materials surged 15.6% during the three months to the end of September, curbing operating profit growth.

news.title: Centre on verge of launching long-term leasing out of ITDC hotels
news.para: However, it is not known if all the Ashok Group of Hotels which are 100 per cent owned by the India Tourism Development Corporation (ITDC) will be leased via a single bidding process.

news.title: UK house prices show unexpected strength in October: Nationwide
news.para: Mortgage lender Nationwide said house prices rose by 0.7% in monthly terms in October after a 0.2% rise in September. A Reuters poll of economists had pointed to another 0.2% increase.

news.title: Weakening finances of Chinese developers put pressure on Beijing to act
news.para: Evergrande's long-drawn debt crisis has not spilled into China's broader financial markets as feared, but the worsening health of China's $5 trillion property sector is testing Beijing's resolve to press on with painful structural reforms.

news.title: China's Kaisa Group sales dip 30.5% to $1.28 billion in October 2021
news.para: Kaisa said late on Wednesday its October contracted sales dropped 30.5% to 8.195 billion yuan ($1.28 billion) from a year ago, while sales in the first 10 months rose 23%.

news.title: Abu Dhabi's Aldar Properties' net profit rises 11% in Q3 2021
news.para: Profit attributable to shareholders came in at 473.2 million dirhams ($128.85 million) for the three months ended Sept. 30, compared with 426.2 million dirhams in the prior-year period.

news.title: Evergrande says 57,400 properties handed to buyers between July-October
news.para: As one of China's biggest property developers, fears around Evergrande's debt mountain have battered investor sentiment and shaken the country's mammoth real estate market.

news.title: Check rising construction material costs: Builders
news.para: The developers said the hike in raw material cost in the past six months had derailed their project estimations and they were not able to finish a project within the agreed upon cost.
